cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the compression of neural networks. Additionally, since the paper focuses on compressing neural networks for mobile devices, it is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves knowledge transfer from a teacher network, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Furthermore, since the paper deals with computational and memory bottlenecks, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
